<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-04-20T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-04-20T19:00:00-05:00" n="93" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d93">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.34119/1313: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-20T19:00:00-05:00">April 20, 1938—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>51. For Braden. Your 93, April 19, 3 p.m. The Department approves of your
                            remaining in Buenos Aires until the termination of the present phase of
                            the negotiations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>